The paper discusses the incorporation of additional information within machine learning algorithms, specifically in the context of unsupervised learning and data clustering. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of privileged information and the exploration of the difference between privileged and technical data also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) or Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the application of the proposed method to the task of digit recognition suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SI).
